Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.53,0:01:01.66,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Yomigaeru GANDAMU!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.83,0:01:08.00,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,You must seize the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.83,0:01:08.00,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Kimi yo tsukame
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.38,0:01:14.97,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Fly toward the galaxy, Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.38,0:01:14.97,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Ginga e mukatte tobeyo GANDAMU
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:21.39,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam! Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.05,0:01:21.39,Lyrics,,0,0,0,,Kidou senshi GANDAMU! GANDAMU!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.12,0:01:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the year 0079 of the Universal Century.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.41,0:01:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Giant space cities have been built\Naround the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.76,0:01:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,As each group of colonies was completed,\Nit was given a number. Side 1 . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.09,0:01:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .Side 2, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years after\Nthe seventh Side was built. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.22,0:01:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .war broke out between the Principality\Nof Zeon and the Earth Federation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.68,0:01:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Four Sides were destroyed\Nduring the fighting. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.10,0:01:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .and only Side 6 remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.20,0:02:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The White Base, with its young crew. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.73,0:02:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . is now making its way across\NCentral Asia toward Europe. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .destroying M'Quve's\Nmining bases as it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.70,0:02:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trap of M'Quve
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.14,0:02:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He came out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.76,0:02:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn, l missed him !
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bright's not going to be too happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.99,0:02:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bright, Magella Attacks are\Nspreading out to starboard !
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.24,0:02:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bright, your orders. . .?\Nls something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.76,0:02:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No. . . I'm fine. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.82,0:02:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Have the Gundam. . . No. . .\NHave the Guntank take care of defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.83,0:02:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.05,0:03:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Resistance from the enemy base\Nhas completely subsided.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.46,0:03:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,ls that right. . .\NOrder the Gundam and the Guntank to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.89,0:03:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off quickly as soon as\Nthey're safely aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.86,0:03:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright, what course should l set?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.74,0:03:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.38,0:04:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.21,0:04:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirai, we're still in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.63,0:04:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Could someone help him up?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.79,0:04:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.37,0:04:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bright. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.69,0:04:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That Elran doesn't give me\Nvery much useful information.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.48,0:04:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Your regular report, sir{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.45,0:04:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What Is It, sir?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.78,0:04:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this l hear about the loss of\NBauxite Mining Bases No. 7 and No. 86?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The defenses we had\Nshould have been adequate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.58,0:04:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the attacks of the Trojan Horse and Its}.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.76,0:04:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.\NI'll take care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.09,0:05:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, sir{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.14,0:05:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Judock. Go tell General Elran this. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.77,0:05:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For the entire day tomorrow. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.27,0:05:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . he must slow down the movement of\NFederation forces in Eastern Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.32,0:05:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. l understand, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mr. Judock.\N- Yes, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.79,0:05:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Fix your uniform.\NYour Federation collar is showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.30,0:05:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice and clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you !
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.64,0:05:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Settle down !
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.39,0:05:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.52,0:05:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,See, l warned you !
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you have to rinse off completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.40,0:05:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.90,0:05:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Kikka are both girls, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.61,0:05:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.61,0:05:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why is Kikka so flat here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Naughty boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.85,0:06:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.79,0:06:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you get me\Nreplacement part No. 1 33?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.98,0:06:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.52,0:06:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- Isn't it there?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.42,0:06:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the Medea delivered it the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.15,0:06:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't replace it, it'll still work. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.31,0:06:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . but it's a class D consumable part,\Nso the unit will be much less reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been put away somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask Mr. Bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go too. There're other parts\Nl have to talk to him about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.46,0:06:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.95,0:06:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hi.\N- Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.75,0:06:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- My. . .\N- What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You two stink.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.84,0:06:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's true! You really stink!\N- Phew!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.88,0:06:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stinky!\N- So stinky!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.35,0:06:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You two should at least use the shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.99,0:07:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.74,0:07:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,See you. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you filthy creatures!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.03,0:07:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Filthy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.41,0:07:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Mr. Bright?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.62,0:07:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in the infirmary. What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.40,0:07:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then. . .where's Ms. Mirai?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She's checking on Mr. Bright\Nin the infirmary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.33,0:07:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We really need her here now.\NShe should let Sunmalo take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.81,0:07:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.54,0:07:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The hangar's this way, Amuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll drop by the infirmary and ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.29,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'll wait for you in the hangar, then.\N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The fever isn't going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,l gave him a sedative just now.\NIt'll come down soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.91,0:07:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Amuro. ls there something you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.15,0:07:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.58,0:07:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- So, did you ask about the parts?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.22,0:08:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice! They'll be passing over us\Nany moment now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.06,0:08:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,l want you all\Nto check your equipment again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.59,0:08:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't carry even a sliver of metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.18,0:08:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Lang, take off your watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.27,0:08:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all plastic,\Nlike the rest of the equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.77,0:08:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, put on your lift jets!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.45,0:08:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- How's the gas pressure in the lift jets?\N- We're all okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.78,0:08:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We checked it before too.\NI'm sure it's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.59,0:08:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.69,0:08:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys are in for a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.89,0:08:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't detect us at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.97,0:08:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Lang, keep your mouth shut\Nuntil we've succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.93,0:09:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.57,0:10:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, according to the computer,\Nit's just exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.49,0:10:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be all right\Nafter 2 or 3 days of rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.61,0:10:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,l see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.60,0:10:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- How did it go?\N- Don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.54,0:11:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.42,0:11:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,An explosion. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.72,0:11:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.01,0:11:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They got us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.63,0:11:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,l don't know how they did it, but\Nthey got our Minovsky particle emitters. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.22,0:11:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .and the E.C. M. transmitters!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.48,0:11:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That means. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.81,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We're completely vulnerable\Nto the enemy's sensors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.03,0:11:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the radar?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.40,0:11:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's undamaged.\Nl wonder why they didn't destroy it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.25,0:11:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,l don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.45,0:11:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Mirai, please don't think that\Nthe operators overlooked something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.10,0:11:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,l would never. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.30,0:11:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Operators, sound the alarm anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.30,0:11:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Put everyone on level 2 battle stations.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.21,0:12:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn ! No more time\Nfor replacing parts!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.26,0:12:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Incoming!\NFormation of 20 Dopp-like aircraft!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.96,0:12:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be fighters! Amuro! Ryu. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.23,0:12:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Amuro! Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.52,0:12:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Launch Core Fighters, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.78,0:12:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.21,0:12:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.27,0:12:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please hurry with the Core Fighter launch!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.26,0:12:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato! I'll go ahead !
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.09,0:12:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But we should stay close together\Nwhen we fight. Got it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Roger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.77,0:12:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Another Dopp formation !
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding, Amuro!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.19,0:12:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Two Core Fighters are no match against that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.77,0:12:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,l agree! What was she thinking\Nwhen she deployed the Core Fighters?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.99,0:13:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Another formation incoming !\NCourse, 27 0! Speed, Mach 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.99,0:13:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Altitude, 1 2,000! About 1 5 fighters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.62,0:13:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we deploy the Guntank\Nto the rear for cover?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.79,0:13:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way we can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.80,0:13:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,First wave, at 1 2 o'clock, directly overhead !
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.14,0:13:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Amuro! Hayato!\NCover the White Base!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.27,0:13:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.95,0:13:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good ! There're too many of them !
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.63,0:13:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't, Mr. Bright!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.55,0:13:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- To the bridge. . .\N- You're kidding ! Not in your condition !
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.14,0:13:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why can't I move my body?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.22,0:13:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Am I afraid?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.39,0:14:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryu. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryu ! Cover the port side\Nwith the Guncannon !
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bright. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.49,0:14:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll launch the Gundam\Nand Guntank parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.53,0:14:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Please inform the mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirai! You're making them\Ndo a mid-air transfer. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.11,0:14:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .without the Gunperry,\Nand during battle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.20,0:14:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,ls that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.45,0:14:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If deploying the Core Fighters\Nwas a mistake. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . l have to correct it right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.00,0:14:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirai, l think Amuro is capable of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.00,0:14:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hayato. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can have Hayato transfer\Non the White Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.98,0:14:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfect, Sayla.\NWe'll do both at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.89,0:14:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! A mid-air transfer during battle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How am l supposed to do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.36,0:14:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that.\NWe're launching the Gundam parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.28,0:14:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato, return to the White Base\Nand transfer to the Guncannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.08,0:14:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you use Mr. Kai?\NHe's right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.28,0:15:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. . . Kai's on the anti-air turrets\Nand can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.24,0:15:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,l understand.\NPlease launch the Gundam parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.08,0:15:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't blame me if the Gundam gets hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.50,0:15:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going too fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,l wish they'd consider my situation !
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensor synchronized !
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.32,0:15:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Launching A Parts!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.78,0:15:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're rushing too much !
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Gundam ! Here l go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our plan to flush out the Trojan Horse. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.40,0:16:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . is proceeding quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful, Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.95,0:16:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They've spread a net on the ground as well.\NGot it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.74,0:16:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No one told us the Zeons had\Nsuch a powerful force in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.76,0:16:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We just have to accept reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.21,0:16:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Marker! Can you find us an escape route?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.51,0:16:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,7 0 degrees to starboard\Nis relatively clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.34,0:16:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.14,0:16:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And they don't even know why\Nwe let them keep their radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.39,0:16:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they have the radar. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.89,0:16:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .they analyze the situation\Nand fall into our trap on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.27,0:16:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,- Impressive as always, Captain.\N- l suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.13,0:16:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.63,0:17:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm out of ammo! I'll just have to. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.46,0:17:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.44,0:17:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato! Does the Guncannon\Nhave any ammo left?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.94,0:17:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- That was the last!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.13,0:17:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You !
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.94,0:18:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't take much more of this.\NWhere's the White Base?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.08,0:18:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato! Let's jump and get out of here!\NAll right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.17,0:18:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Two enemy mobile suits\Nhave escaped from our encirclement!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.47,0:18:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well. We'll just finish them\Nalong with the Trojan Horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been hit in Blocks 1 3 and 1 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.45,0:18:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the engines all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.30,0:18:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- We can still fly!\N- Then we're going to run !
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.06,0:18:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,ls running all you think about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.39,0:18:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the best l can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.95,0:18:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What more do you want from me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.79,0:18:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,l wish Ryu were here at a time like this. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.16,0:18:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Gundam and Guncannon, back on board !
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.71,0:18:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can they do another sortie, Sayla?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.67,0:18:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask. l doubt it's possible, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Sayla! How long do you think it takes\Nto replenish our weapons and energy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.14,0:19:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Please think reasonably\Nabout the situation !
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.47,0:19:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Amuro, that's going too far{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We're giving orders situation{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.06,0:19:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going out as soon as\Nthe beam rifle's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! It'll be about 2 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.89,0:19:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If only Ryu were here now. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayato! Don't say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.33,0:19:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. . .Good. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.87,0:19:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in a little bit further.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange. The Dopps are withdrawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.67,0:19:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.81,0:19:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to get out of here now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.89,0:19:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Go after the Dopps! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.89,0:20:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us shut down main engine No. 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.02,0:20:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll explode at this rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.06,0:20:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Pressure build-up in the third nozzle\Nof main engine No. 1 .
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.98,0:20:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to shut it down, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.91,0:20:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was that mega particle cannon !
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.12,0:20:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it out. . . in one shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.42,0:20:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying, Mirai?\NYou're in command now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,l can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.11,0:21:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're done for. . .\N- Ms. Mirai. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.37,0:21:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! The attack force is returning !
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.00,0:21:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to finish us off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.00,0:21:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,l have an idea!\Nl don't know if this will work, but. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.08,0:21:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Huh?\N- Ms. Sayla. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.50,0:21:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We take the safety off the smoke bombs. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.58,0:21:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .and set them off in the launch tubes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.76,0:21:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll be a lot of damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.67,0:21:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we can fool the enemy, we'll survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.05,0:21:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mirai?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.65,0:21:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave it to you. l. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.66,0:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.44,0:21:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryu. . . ! Help me. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.41,0:21:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Bright. . . ! Ryu. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.74,0:21:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me. . . !
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.25,0:22:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh ! They're off the radar!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.76,0:22:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We're safe for now. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.30,0:22:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.22,0:22:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the only thing we can do\Nis ask General Revil for support.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.10,0:22:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it shows up. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.11,0:22:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the battle status?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.07,0:22:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Mirai?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.18,0:22:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We made it through somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.19,0:22:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But will we arrive in time for Odessa Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.82,0:22:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Odessa Day. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.57,0:22:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the counter-offensive\Nin Europe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.13,0:22:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.09,0:22:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sayla!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.73,0:22:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please send a coded message\Nto General Revil of the Federation Forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.45,0:23:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A Medea transport team is\Nassaulted by Goufs. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.36,0:23:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,. . .scattering relief supplies in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.79,0:23:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the Gundam, joining in the fight,\Nis damaged by the Gouf's powerful attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.55,0:23:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,After delivering the G Parts from\Nthe transport plane, Matilda cries. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.34,0:23:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Rise up, Amuro!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.64,0:23:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile Suit Gundam. Next episode...\NMatilda's Rescue.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.84,0:23:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Matilda's Rescue
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.68,0:23:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be able to survive?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.19,0:23:54.03,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Amuro, do not look back
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.03,0:23:59.03,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,The star shining far off in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.03,0:24:09.25,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Amuro, it's your homeland\Nwhere you were born
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.25,0:24:14.18,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Do you remember the days\Nof your childhood?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.18,0:24:18.81,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,The morning when you woke up in warmth?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.81,0:24:24.19,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Amuro, do not look back, Amuro...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.19,0:24:28.77,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,A man must hide his tears, hide his tears
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.77,0:24:39.08,Lyrics Top,,0,0,0,,Only look to tomorrow, to tomorrow\NForever...
